This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it proposes a novel decision-making method for decentralized coalition formation that exploits probabilistic topic modeling. It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.GT (Game Theory) because it deals with cooperative games and proposes a novel representation scheme for such games. Additionally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it uses online Latent Dirichlet Allocation for topic modeling. It may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with relations among agents and their collaboration structures. Finally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because it proposes a new representation scheme for cooperative games.
